PCRE2_SET_HEAP_LIMIT(3)    Library Functions Manual    PCRE2_SET_HEAP_LIMIT(3)

NAME
       PCRE2 - Perl-compatible regular expressions (revised API)

SYNOPSIS

       #include <pcre2.h>

       int pcre2_set_heap_limit(pcre2_match_context *mcontext,
         uint32_t value);

DESCRIPTION

       This  function  sets  the backtracking heap limit field in a match con‚Äê
       text. The result is always zero.

       There is a complete description of the PCRE2 native API in the pcre2api
       page and a description of the POSIX API in the pcre2posix page.

